4 L. The functions of the consortium shall be to accomplish all of the
5 following:
6 (1) Develop an initiative known as the Funding Priority Program for
7 Women's Health Initiatives to identify current funding provided for women's health
8 initiatives, recommend funding needed to sustain and enhance current effective
9 initiatives, and identify new funding opportunities to support emerging scientific
10 research and innovation. The identification or recommendation of any public-private
11 partnership, funding opportunity, or collaborative initiative by the consortium shall
12 not authorize or obligate the Louisiana Department of Health or any participating
13 agency to enter into any contract, memorandum of understanding, or financial
14 commitment.
15 (2) Develop an Interagency Women's Health Agenda for recommendations
16 to the Louisiana Department of Health. The agenda shall include but not be limited
17 to all of the following:
18 (a) Strengths, weaknesses, and opportunities in research, access to care,
19 medical education, funding, policy, regulations, public education, and access to
20 information pertaining to women's health at every stage of life.
21 (b) The Funding Priority Program for Women's Health Initiatives.
22 (3) Identify health issues which significantly affect women in this state,
23 including but not limited to perimenopause, menopause, and postmenopause.
24 (4) Identify systemic barriers and health gaps to standard access of quality
25 care across women's health and possible solutions.
26 (5) Evaluate and provide recommendations on:
27 (a) Solutions and partnerships to drive innovation in the diagnosis, treatment,
28 and prevention of women-specific conditions in this state.
29 (b) Training in the delivery of care for medical students and physicians in
30 this state, relating to the health issues which significantly affect women.
